<item>
            <title>[SOLR-3142] remove O(n^2) slow slow indexing defaults in DataImportHandler</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-3142</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;By default, dataimporthandler optimizes the entire index when it commits.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This is bad for performance, because it means by default its doing a very&lt;br/&gt;
heavy index-wide operation even for an incremental update... essentially &lt;br/&gt;
O(n^2) indexing.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;All that is needed is to set optimize=false by default. If someone wants&lt;br/&gt;
to optimize, they can either set optimize=true or explicitly optimize themselves.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12543253">SOLR-3142</key>
            <summary>remove O(n^2) slow slow indexing defaults in DataImportHandler</summary>
